# Website Workflow

This is a Jekyll site (al-folio theme) deployed via GitHub Actions to mariondumas.github.io.

## Iteration loop

1. User describes desired change.
2. Agent researches and presents a plan (Plan mode).
3. User approves; agent switches to Agent mode.
4. Agent edits files, builds locally with `LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8 bundle exec jekyll build`, fixes any errors.
5. Agent commits and pushes to `master` (the deploy workflow builds and force-pushes `gh-pages`).
6. Agent verifies the deploy by checking the live site HTML.
7. User inspects the result and describes the next change.

## Build & deploy

- Local build: `LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8 bundle exec jekyll build`
- Push target: `origin master` (triggers `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`)
- Live site: `https://mariondumas.github.io`
- Deploy branch: `gh-pages` (auto-updated by CI)

## jekyll-scholar queries

The `--sort_by` and `--order` flags break `-q` query parsing in jekyll-scholar 7.1.2.
Use `sort_by` and `order` in `_config.yml` scholar block instead.
For entry-type filters use `@article`, `@unpublished`, etc., not `@*[type=...]`.

## Key files

- `_config.yml` — site config, `max_width`, `scholar:` settings
- `_layouts/bib.html` — bibliography entry template (shared by all pages)
- `_includes/selected_papers.html` — homepage selected papers query
- `_pages/publications.md` — publications page with three-section layout
- `_layouts/about.html` — homepage layout
- `_sass/_layout.scss` — publication and homepage styling
- `_bibliography/papers.bib` — all bibliography entries
